{"parse":{"title":"rice","pageid":4869,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|RICE|Rice|ricé|-rice}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n[[File:Unpolished-rice.jpg|thumb|Unpolished '''rice''' (grains of {{taxfmt|Oryza sativa|species}})]]\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ɹaɪs/}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-rice.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{audio|en|en-uk-rice.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{rhymes|en|aɪs|s=1}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|rys}}, from {{der|en|fro|ris}}, from {{der|en|roa-oit|riso}}, {{m|it|risi}}, from {{der|en|gkm|ὄρυζα}}, from an Eastern {{der|en|ira|-}} language related to {{cog|pal|blnc|tr=*brinǰ}}, {{cog|kmr|riz}} (beyond Euphrates) and {{cog|zza|riz}}. Theorized to come to Iranian languages from {{cog|sa|व्रीहि}}.\n\nPrior to Sanskrit, it is speculated to be possibly a borrowing from a {{der|en|dra}} language (compare {{cog|dra-pro|*wariñci||rice}}), or from {{der|en|aav}} languages further east.\n\nAlternatively {{cog|gkm|ὄρυζα}} is said to be from {{cog|he|אורז|tr=órez}}, from South Arabian ''areez''{{attn|und}} ultimately from {{cog|oty|𑀅𑀭𑀺𑀘𑀺}}.<ref>https://www.tamildigitallibrary.in/admin/assets/book/TVA_BOK_0013043_Proceedings_Of_The_Second_International_Conference_Seminar_Of_Tamil_Studies.pdf pg436</ref>\n\n{{dbt|en|arroz}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}} [[cereal|Cereal]] plants, {{taxfmt|Oryza sativa|species}} of the grass family whose seeds are used as food.\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=The Naturalist|volume=1|page=375|author=Daniel Jay Browne|year=1831|passage='''Rice''' is a tropical plant; yet Carolina and Georgia grow the finest in the world; heavier grained, better filled, and more merchantable, than any imported into Europe from the Indies.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cGhMAAAAYAAJ&dq=%22rice%22%20%22plant%22&pg=PA375#v=onepage&q=%22rice%22%20%22plant%22&f=false}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Drought Resistance in Crops with Emphasis on Rice|year=1982|author=International Rice Research Institute|passage=Drought stress causes yield reductions and sometimes total crop failures in rainfed '''rice''' areas of Asia, Africa, and Latin America.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IDJVhGP9of8C&lpg=PA77&dq=%22rice%20plants%22&pg=PA245#v=onepage&q=rice&f=false}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Transgenic Herbicide Resistance in Plants|author=V. S. Rao|passage='''Rice''' transformed with genes encoding human CYP1a1, CYP2B6, and CYP2C19 are more tolerant of various herbicides than non-transgenic rice plants, due to increased metabolism by the introduced P450 enzymes [Kawwahigashi et al. 2005a, 2007, 2008; James et al. 2008].|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8IiZBQAAQBAJ&lpg=PA315&dq=%22rice%20plants%22&pg=PA315#v=onepage&q=%22rice%20plants%22&f=false|year=2014}}\n# {{lb|en|countable}} A specific [[variety]] of this plant.\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=The Valley of Kashmír|author=Sir Walter Roper Lawrence|year=1895|passage=The '''rices''' of Kashmír are infinite in variety. In one tahsíl I have found fifty-three varieties.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=chHZSuf1i98C&dq=%22rices%20of%22&pg=PA332#v=onepage&q=%22rices%20of%22&f=false}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|volume=25|date=April 1922|passage=First, we have the Italian '''rices'''; secondly, the '''rices''' of the French colonies of Indo-China and Madagascar, which are beginning to cultivate '''rices''' of very fine quality, altogether superior to those that were cultivated only a few years back.|number=4|title=America Has Hard Competition in France|author=L. Humbert|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GbVHAQAAMAAJ&dq=%22rices%20of%22&pg=RA3-PR48#v=onepage&q=%22rices%20of%22&f=false|journal=Rice Journal and Southern Farmer}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Aromatic Rices|year=2000|passage=For commercial purposes, the '''rices''' are classified according to the kernel length as short-grain, medium-grain, longgrain and long-slender-grain.|editors=R.K Singh; U.S. Singh; G.S. Khush|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fJi0FxyM7pQC&lpg=PA53&dq=%22the%20rices%22&pg=PA53#v=onepage&q=%22the%20rices%22&f=false}}\n# {{senseid|en|Q5090}}{{lb|en|uncountable}} The seeds of this plant used as food.\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Practical Cooking and Dinner Giving|author=Mary Foote Henderson|year=1881|passage=Mold boiled '''rice''', when hot, in cups which have been previously dipped in cold water; when cold, turn them out on a flat dish, arranging them uniformly; then with a tea-spoon scoop out a little of the '''rice''' from the top of each cone, and put in its place any kind of jelly.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=inwEAAAAYAAJ&dq=%22rice%22%20%22cooking%22&pg=PA287#v=onepage&q=%22rice%22%20%22cooking%22&f=false}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1961|author={{w|Harry E. Wedeck}}|title=Dictionary of Aphrodisiacs|publisher=The Citadel Press|location=New York|page=207|passage=In Britain too '''rice''' is reputed to increase the sexual faculties.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Sustainability of Rice in the Global Food System|author=Noreen G. Dowling|year=1998|passage=In sum, when a modern Japanese family and its members sit around the supper table eating their bowls of Japanese-grown '''rice''', they are not simply indulging a gastronomic preference for short-grained and slightly sticky japonica '''rice''' over long-grained indica '''rice''' from Thailand.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ke8p-D2dp5EC&lpg=PA62&dq=%22rice%22%20%22eating%22&pg=PA62#v=onepage&q=%22rice%22%20%22eating%22&f=false}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Rice: Origin, Antiquity and History|author=S. D. Sharma|year=2010|passage=On the festival day, '''rice''' is cooked together with this rice knot above.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hTvNBQAAQBAJ&lpg=PA109&dq=%22rice%22%20%22eating%22&pg=PA110#v=onepage&q=%22rice%22%20%22eating%22&f=false}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|slang|ethnic slur|humorous}} The types of automobile modifications characteristic of a [[rice burner]].\n# {{lb|en|computing|slang}} An instance of [[customization]] of a user interface.\n#: {{ux|en|This is my first '''rice'''!}}\n\n=====Hyponyms=====\n{{col3|en|title=Hyponyms of rice (noun)\n|Ambemohar\n|arborio\n|aromatic rice\n|basmati\n|beaten rice\n|Bhutanese red rice|botan rice|mochi rice|pearl rice\n|black rice\n|bora saul\n|brown rice\n|Calrose rice\n|Camargue red rice\n|carnaroli\n|Champa rice\n|cooked rice\n|flattened rice\n|glutinous rice\n|golden rice\n|jasmine rice\n|Patna rice\n|red rice\n|samba rice\n|longevity rice|basmati rice\n|purple rice\n|sticky rice\n|sweet rice| disco rice|chicken rice|Chinese fermented rice|Chinese fermented sweet rice|Chinese sweet fermented rice|fermented glutinous rice|fermented rice|fermented sticky rice|fermented sweet rice|rice porridge|sticky rice wine|sweet rice wine|Thai fermented rice|Thai fermented sweet rice|Thai sweet fermented rice|Vietnamese fermented glutinous rice|Vietnamese fermented sticky rice|Vietnamese fermented sweet rice\n|waxy rice|converted rice|jungle rice\n|white rice|combination fried rice|corn rice|scorched rice|sushi rice|this this rice|two-dish rice|uncooked rice|Yangzhou fried rice|chipped rice|pounded rice|pressed rice|unhusked rice}}\n\n=====Holonyms=====\n{{col|en\n|bhelpuri\n|California roll\n|dosa\n|gumbo\n|idli\n|jambalaya\n|khir\n|mirin\n|mochi\n|nasi goreng\n|onigiri\n|pad thai\n|paella\n|pilaf,pilau\n|rangoli\n|rijsttafel\n|risotto\n|sake\n|samshu\n|sushi\n|tahdig\n}}\n\n=====Coordinate terms=====\n{{list:Cereals/en}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|nonrice|riceburger|ricefield|ricefish|ricegrass|ricegrower|riceland|riceless|ricelike|ricemeal|riceroot|ricey\n|{{vern|African rice}}|ant rice|arborio rice,Arborio rice|artificial rice\n|baby rice|black rice|brewers' rice,brewer's rice|broken rice|brown rice\n|cauliflower rice|cheese and rice|claypot rice|cook-up rice|Coues' rice rat\n|dirty rice|rice steamer\n|economy rice\n|flattened rice|forbidden rice|French rice|fried rice|fried rice syndrome\n|glorified rice|golden rice\n|Hainanese chicken rice|hanging rice|hom mali rice|hungry rice\n|Indian rice|iron rice bowl|Italian rice ball\n|Japanese rice ball|jollof rice\n|like white on rice|longevity rice|long rice\n|Manchurian wild rice|mealie rice|Mexican rice|mountain rice\n|northern wild rice\n|oily rice|omu rice,omu-rice\n|Patna rice|peas and rice|polished rice|pudding rice|puffed rice|purple rice\n|red yeast rice\n|rice and peas\n|rice bag|rice ball|rice bean|ricebird|rice biscuit|rice blast|rice bowl|rice box|rice burner\n|rice cake|rice car|ricecel|rice chaser|rice Christian|rice congee|rice cooker|rice cracker,rice-cracker|rice cutgrass\n|rice eater,rice-eater\n|rice field|rice flakes|rice flour|rice flower\n|rice glue|rice grass|rice growing\n|rice hat|rice hen|rice hull|rice huller|rice husk|rice husker\n|rice king|rice vermicelli\n|rice leafhopper\n|rice malt|rice milk|rice-mill,rice mill|rice moth\n|rice nigger|rice noodle\n|rice out\n|rice paddle|rice paddy|rice paddy herb|rice paper|rice-paper plant|rice pounder|rice pudding\n|rice-queen,rice queen\n|ricer|rice rat|rice rocket\n|rice sheath mite|rice shell|rice-spirit|rice stick|rice stitch|rice swift\n|rice tenrec\n|rice vinegar\n|rice water|rice weevil|rice wine\n|Spanish rice|special fried rice|sticky rice|sweet fermented rice\n|taco rice|thunder tea rice\n|white on rice|white rice|wild rice|rice beer}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n{{top2}}\n* {{desc|rop|rais}}\n* {{desc|bzj|rais}}\n* {{desc|bi|raes}}\n* {{desc|kri|rɛs}}\n* {{desc|mi|raihi}}\n* {{desc|tpi|rais}}\n* {{desc|ja|ライス|tr=raisu|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|mkj|rais|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{trans-top|plants}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Abaza: {{tt|abq|прунджь}}\n* Abkhaz: {{tt|ab|абрынџь}}, {{tt|ab|апрынџь}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|rys}}\n* Akan: {{t|ak|ɛmo}}\n* Aklanon: {{t|akl|paeay}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|oriz|m}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{tt|alt|рис}}\n* Amharic: {{t|am|ሩዝ|tr=ruzi}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|أَرُزّ|m}}, {{tt+|ar|رُزّ|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|رز|m-p|tr=ruzz}}\n*: Hassaniya Arabic: {{t|mey|مارو|m|tr=mā